de_clashpoint
Mapped for CS:Source by Andrew Du
studio@sixdimensional.com

Map Description:

This map is purely fictional, however the location has been derived from the London Canary Wharf finance area.
The map hosts a situation where terrorsits have attempted to move explosives into the area and set them off to leave the city in financial ruin, however have been stopped from moving these around through counter-intelligence. Their new aim is to do as much damage as possible using "Clashpoints" under some of the area's buildings.

There are two clashpoints on this map:
1) There is a clashpoint in a small office close to the Docklands tower. This is located at the base of the Canary Wharf building.
2) There is a warehouse that hosts a lot of documents to which could also be destroyed in order to bring about a long financial halt. This could also be destroyed.

As with any "de_" map, the terrorists are the ones with the explosives, the the counter-terrorists are out to stop them.

I've also added a secret access area which has reasonable access from both terrorists and counter terrorists. It's not very obvious, but it's quite rewarding. If you manage to find this out then you can tell me about it, studio@sixdimensional.com - well done.

Welcome to Eindhoven. - Het Stadhuisplein - 

A fairly large city in the Netherlands. Known for Philips, innovative technology and a great atmosphere.
Sadly though, a war has broken out and it has left Eindhoven in ruins. 
Eindhoven has al lot of strategic value because of its airfield and good connections to the rest of the Netherlands.

A monumental piece of Eindhoven, called 'het stadhuisplein' still stands. 
But the terrorist are planning to change that..
Their plan is to destroy the cityhall of Eindhoven!!

=========
Terrorists:

Plant a bomb on the center of the square, so it will destroy the city hall.

CITY GATES
by Randy Cotter

My second map with hammer and I think i've created a map with a lot of potential...

City Gates puts the terrorists and the counter terrorists on opposite sides of a massive defensive structure, guarding the entrance to a hidden city.  The most impressive feature of this map is it's TWO HUNDRED spawn points (half and half) leaving the possibility for MASSIVE multiplayer battles.  The army of terrorists have one goal-- bomb the massive gate built into the fortress wall, while the counter terrorists must use all means to prevent the bomb from going off.  Terrorists have lots of cover from the oppressive firepower raining down from the looming walls.  CT's have two sniping bunkers to use and also have massive boulder defenses which can be released to crush approaching enemies.  

This map was a lot of work for me. Not sure how many hours, but it was a lot more than de_fireinthehole (it is my second map, so im still learning, but I think it's pretty good) ;)  

Spread the word about the 200 player capability and hopefully we'll see some HUGE games in the near future (on servers that can handle it!!!!)

This is the first release of my new css map de_cityfever_beta (I know, it is still beta and it contains a lot of bugs). There are over 2 Months and 200 hours of work to get this map done. Hopefully the map is the work worth.

Made for the German eSports magazine eFever.
Standard Half-Life 2 Setting (City/Urban) without the Combine

It’s made in cooperation with the German online magazine eFever.de.
